Title: Agnarr's Jarlin: Abandoned on Niflheim 2 (A Monster Romance With Space Orc Vikings)
Author: Jenifer Wood
My Review:
**I received an ARC of Agnarr's Jarlin. Below is my honest review.**

I really loved this story! Agnarr's Teacher was a complete surprise when I read it and I have recommended it to everyone I know. So to say I was looking forward to this is an understatement. I normally don't like second books that follow the same romance as the first book but this is a clear exception! There is so much more for Piper and Agnarr to go thru in this book and neither character regresses, which is something that bothers me about other sequel romance books. You will not find that here. They grow even more as couple as they step into their new roles which is why I think this works so well. It also sets up the other characters for future books in the series, which has me even more excited to come back to this world.

I recently described Agnarr's Teacher as "cozy smut" and I will officially add Agnarr's Jarlin to the subgenre as well.

Title: Star Spear (Sun Serpent Saga, #2)
Author: Geneva Monroe
My Review:
Sun Serpent came out of nowhere and surprised me. Star Spear decided to one up Sun Serpent and was everything I wanted in a book and more! I'm going to be screaming this book's praises all over social media! Geneva has caused my skin to crawl on The Steps, my heart to break, my nerves to be shot, and made me laugh at the amazing banter between characters! I literally put the book down for 24 hours with 6 chapters left because she had built the story in such a way that my heart was in my throat and I was ready for the sky to fall in the last chapters. They did not disappoint but MAN was it a ride. I need a long nap and a massage to get all of this tension out of my shoulders! Woo!

Cannot recommend enough! I have a feeling I will read every book Geneva writes! What an amazing debut series!

**I received an advanced reader copy from the author. This review is fully my own.**

And can we talk about Xoc?! This is me hoping she writes some POV from his perspective. I'll be jealous of the character who ends up with him. Cannot wait to read Star Spear!!!

Title: The Seven Year Slip
Author: Ashley Poston
My Review: She did it again! Dead Romantics was one of my top three books I read in 2022. And The Seven Year Slip is now one of my top books of 2023. Within the first 5 pages, Ashley creates a magical, mysterious, and evocative world. I got the same tingling feeling reading this book that I did with Dead Romantics and it was such a treat when **spoiler** a certain man named Benji makes an appearance. A lot of romance writers create their own universes where all the characters from all their books live in the same world, but Ashley makes it feel new and exciting. I don't know any other author out there doing what she does. Cannot wait for her next book!

Title: The True Love Experiment
Author: Christina Lauren
My Review:
First things first, I received an ARC of this book. Okay now let's get into the review!

This is the third Christina Lauren book I have read.i read Unhoneymooners last year and I read The Soulmate Equation about a week ago. I actually enjoyed Soulmate Equation better than Unhoneymooners so when I got this arc I was so excited because I couldn't wait to learn more about Fizzy! This book had me laughing from the very beginning to the very end! It was so wonderful and I read it in just over a day. By far my favorite Christina Lauren book so far! I have read other dating show books (Charm Offensive, One to Watch) and I was worried this would be exactly the same. But this book does a great job of not feeling like every other Bachelor/Bachelorette themed book.

I highly recommend to any romance reader! Fizzy and Connor are definitely two of my favorite romantic leads now

Title: Den of Vipers
Author: K.A. Knight
My Review: Most books I read don't get a 2 star review. If I finish the book, it atleast held my interest to warrant 2.5 or 3 stars. But after the major(?) conflict resolved around the 75% mark, I wasn't sure why I was still reading anything. I thought "well maybe this is a book where the last 10% is a preview of their next book." NOPE! Listen, I enjoyed the spice. But if I have to hear "We are vipers" or "I am a viper" again, I will pull my hair out. I stopped reading with 55 pages left to read. And you know what? I don't think I missed anything. I'm not sure who K.A. Knight has editing and beta reading their books, but they need better people. This felt like a sloppy draft that hadn't been edited to make it readable.

Author: Sara Desai
My Review:
Okay listen, I loved this book! I liked it a WHOLE lot more than The Marriage Game. The only reason this didn't get 5 stars was because as a hockey fan, I could not handle when they said halftime FOUR TIMES IN FIVE PAGES! There is no half time in hockey! I can understand one slip, I can understand if the author didn't catch this, but the editors and the publisher?! How did so many people miss this?! There are three periods. There are two intermissions. There is NO HALFTIME!!!

Okay rant over. Besides that, I loved this book

Title: The Bodyguard
Author: Katherine Center
My Review: I got an advanced copy of this book in my Book of the Month subscription box. I really enjoyed it! Do I normally like my rom coms spicier? Yes. But was this a fantastic read  that I basically read in a day? Yes! I really liked the character development and how the story moved. The one critism I have is that the MC is established as a bad ass who is always aware of her surroundings but as soon as she gets to the ranch it feels like all of that character development goes out the window. I know why they did it for the story but I didnt like what it did for the characters. Besides that, this was a fantastic book. Definitely recommend!

My Review:
Sometimes a book comes out of nowhere and hits you right in the core. This book did that for me. I've been reading a lot of romance and rom com novels recently and they have started to feel the same. This one felt different. There was magic between these characters, there was a story I haven't seen. There were places I've never been. I got completely lost in this one. I received an advanced review copy for free and I am looking leaving this review voluntarily. But I also loved it so much I'm purchasing my own copy so I can reread this amazing story.

Title: The Charm Offensive (The Charm Offensive, #1)
Author: Alison Cochrun
My Review:
Queer representation? Check!
Mental illness/health representation? Check!
Neurodivergent representation? Check!

This book covered it all but not in the way to just hit on them, but more to make these real living characters. These characters feel so three dimensional, it's hard not to feel like you are friends with them by the end of the book. Super fast and fun read and really let's the audience feel seen. Thank you for this gem of a book!

Title: The Seven Husbands of Evelyn Hugo
Author: Taylor Jenkins Reid

Title: Ties That Tether
Author: Jane Igharo
My Review: If you love rom coms, you will love this book. If you want more diversity in your reading, you will love this book. If you love a quick read that will keep you up all night, with the "will they? won't they?", you will love this book. I loved this book. Does it have some troupes? Absolutely but it also leans into them and knows that they are there. It is just as much a story about family and immigration and forgiveness as it is about love. This is the perfect book to take on vacation and make you feel all of the feels. Even though I knew how some of it would go, I still cried. Excellent writing.

Title: The Immortality Trials (The Immortality Trials Trilogy #1)
Author: Madison   Nicole
My Review:
Wow! I will first be upfront that I received an ARC of this book this week when I came across Madison's TikTok.

Let me say that this book was incredible and everything I wanted out of an urban fantasy novel. Think Triwizard Tournament meets Hunger Games meets the second half of ACOTAR. Add in found family, strong world building, and a story that sucks you in and keeps you up late reading and truly feels like a new adult novel. I mean, what more could I have possibly want in a book?!

I can't wait to see what comes next from Madison Nicole and if this is her debut novel, then I think she is one to watch!

So highly recommend! Go pre-order this book! I honestly believe you will love it!

Title: It Ends with Us (It Ends with Us, #1)
Author: Colleen Hoover
My Review:
Read the content warnings for this book before reading.

I'm going to be honest here. This book was not for me. It felt like Hoover wrote down any and every traumatic thing she could think of and was like "let's make these plot points!" It honestly felt like she was trying to be shocking for the sake of being shocking. Maybe this book is for some people but it wasn't for me. I'm honestly not sure if I would read another Hoover book if they are all like this.

Title: The Awakening (Zodiac Academy, #1)
Author: Caroline Peckham
My Review: Is this the best written series? No. Did I also stay up until 4am reading it? Yes! You will definitely get sucked into these and as long as you know going in that this will not be the best written series, I think you will have fun reading them too.

Title: One Last Stop
Author: Casey McQuiston
My Review: Loved this book. I had already read Red, White, and Royal Blue so I was excited to read this. Honestly, I love this book way more! I love the added genre on top of romance (won't spoil it for you). The queer history in the book is well done and really felt like a lovely way of honoring our queer siblings who came before us. Highly recommend!
